    <h2><b>NAUTICAL SICENCE</b></h2>
    <p>Take a two hour educational journey aboard the Spirit of Buffalo. This trip is focused on Nautical Science and the history of our surrounding area. Students will participate in hands on activities including: team building (sail setting), navigation, mechanical advantage with use of simple machines, buoyancy, nautical terminology
and sail theory. </p>
    <p>This trip is hands on, using small groups on board. </p>
    <p style="font-size:1.1em; font-weight:900; padding-left:40px; text-align:left;">Capacity 30<br />
    2 hour Program - $650</p>
    
   <h2><b>FIELD TRIP</b></h2>
   <p>This two hour trip is designed for larger groups.  Our on board educator will give a narration with question and answer periods throughout. We will include topics such as nautical terminology, Buffalo’s waterfront history, types of vessels that used the Buffalo Harbor, sail theory. Other topics can be incorporated to the trip, let us know what you would like to be covered so we could cater the trip for your needs.</p>
   
   <p style="font-size:1.1em; font-weight:900; padding-left:40px; text-align:left;">Capacity 40<br />
2 hour trip - $550</p>
